  "narrative" : "Three traditions arrived independently at the same dissolution of the substantial self. Hume looked and found only a bundle of perceptions, the Buddhist tradition found anatta (no fixed owner), and Whitehead found a society of occasions stable enough to appear permanent. Parfit's thought experiments confirm the gradient: identity is not a fact but a convention. The self is a wave that convinced itself it was water.",
